This paper deals with the construction and defense of P2P networks, which involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), and security (cs.CR). The use of game theory (cs.GT) to model the interaction between defender and attacker agents further supports these categories. Finally, the practical application of the approach to the Bitcoin P2P network suggests a potential fit with the social and information networks category (cs.SI).
